##DESCRIPTION
##KEYWORDS('derivatives', 'velocity', 'distance')
##TYPE('word problem')
##COMMENTS:
##  Given equation for the distance of the ball thrown upward,
##  find the maximum height that the ball reaches and
##  its velocity when it hits the ground.
##ENDDESCRIPTION

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"extraAnswerEvaluators.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

 
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Problem 18, Section 3.4 page 135. $BR$BR

Let \(s(t) = 3t^2+2t-5\) for \(0\leq t \leq 1\)  denote  the position of an object moving along a line. Find $BR$BR

(a) The velocity at time \(t\) $SPACE \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR$BR

(b) The acceleration at time  \(t\) $SPACE \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR$BR

(c) Find where the object starts   $SPACE \{ans_rule(20) \} 
$BR$BR
and where it stops  $SPACE \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR$BR
Find the total distance traveled by the object  $SPACE \{ans_rule(20) \}

$BR$BR
(d) Find where the object is accelerating 
   $SPACE \{ans_rule(20) \}
$PAR
 Write the answer above in interval notation. 
$BBOLD Note: $EBOLD
If the answer includes more than one interval write the intervals separated by the "union" symbol, U. 
If needed enter \(\infty\) as $BITALIC infinity $EITALIC and \(-\infty \) as $BITALIC -infinity $EITALIC .


$BR
EOT

$ansa = "6*t+2";
$ansb = "6";
$ansc1 = -5;
$ansc2 = 0;
$ansc3 = 5;
$ansd = "[0,1]";

&ANS(fun_cmp($ansa,var =>'t'));
&ANS(fun_cmp($ansb,var =>'t'));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ansc1));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ansc2));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ansc3));
&ANS(interval_cmp($ansd));

 
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
